Dear HBS Alumni: See the New Houston METRO Train!
Please join the HBS Club for a luncheon with Robert Miller, the Chairman of METRO on Wednesday, September 19th.
METRO was created in 1978 and currently has over 3600 employees.
METRO plays a major role in construction projects throughout Houston and is involved in the $250 million Downtown/Midtown Transit Street project.
Robert Miller will be discussing the long-term plan for METRO and highlighting the new light rail system.
There will be a short video on the project followed by a presentation by Robert Miller.
